<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan Province Starts Rehabilitation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- As the water level of
Dongting Lake dropped below the danger mark, the work of
reconstruction in central China's Hunan Province has begun in full
swing.
</P>
<P>
Many flood-affected people today left their temporary shelters
on the levees for their homes, and the local government has sent
work teams to every flooded region to discuss programs to rebuild
towns and villages with them.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, local governments have also organized farmers to
plant autumn and winter crops, and provided them with seed
strains, chemical fertilizers and necessary funds.
</P>
<P>
More than 21 million flood victims in Hunan, about one third of
the local population, were affected by this summer's devastating
floods on the Yangtze and Dongting Lake, according to a local
official.
</P>
<P>
Statistics available show that direct industrial and
agricultural losses totalled 32.9 billion yuan (3.97 billion US
dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
