<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WFP Grants Zambia Money to Mitigate Disasters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Programme
(WFP) Tuesday granted the disaster management division in the
vice-president's office of Zambia to strengthen its capacity in
mitigating natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
Boniface Nonde, permanent secretary at the Ministry of Finance,
signed on behalf of the Zambian government the agreement and said that
the money was intended for information, resource and inventory
management including community training in the implementation of
mitigating the activities in natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed, out of the total allocation, over half would go
towards meeting the cost of food commodities.
</P>
<P>
Nonde said the El Nino weather phenomenon did a lot of damage
to Zambia's agricultural output in the last season and ruined the
economic infrastructure in the society.
</P>
<P>
WFP representative in Zambia, Techeste Zergaber expressed his
hope that the funds could be used to help Zambian farmers
especially those adversely affected by the El Nino phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
He said the development of an information system on disaster
management in Zambia was important because it would be able to
gauge the government's efforts towards effective management of
such calamities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
