<HEADLINE> UN System Launches International Appeal for Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) said on Tuesday
that most of the funds will be used for food and emergency aid,
and will help people prepare for the coming Winter.
</P>
<P>
As a component of the appeal, UNDP is asking for 1.4 million
U.S. dollars to improve living conditions for the local
population in Tropoje, a poor district in Albania where a large
concentration of refugees from Kosovo now reside.
</P>
<P>
The support will enable local authorities to better cope
with the influx of refugees and respond to their needs.  
