<HEADLINE> Bonn Donates Relief Aid to Flood Victims in China, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- German Ministry for Economic
Cooperation and Development announced Tuesday that it would
provide relief supplies worth 30 million marks (17.6 million U.S.
dollars) to help people hit by the recent floods in China and
Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The German relief supplies would include drinking water
purification equipment, pumps, offroad vehicles as well as medical
supplies, a statement issued by the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the German development ministry estimated that
at least 20 million marks (11.8 million dollars) of the relief
supplies would go to flooding areas in China. But the actual
proportions to be received by the two countries would be
determined by German experts according to the needs on the scene,
he added.  
</P>
