<DOCNO> XIE19980916.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-15 17:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC Determined to Remove Trade Barriers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of
the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) Jamil Al-Hujailan said
Tuesday that the council is determined to make special efforts
to remove hurdles blocking commercial exchanges among member
states, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Al-Hujailan was speaking to reporters after the GCC Committee
of Commercial Cooperation closed its 25th meeting here.
Ministers of Commerce of the six-member GCC attended the
one-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said the GCC ministers of commerce discussed hurdles in
trade exchanges, regulating the retail and whole sale trade,
ownership and trading of shares by the GCC nationals.
</P>
<P>
"The ministers support the establishment of a general audit
authority and this is a crucial matter as auditing has
become an effective factor in reviving and organizing the
economy," Al-Hujailan said.
</P>
<P>
The GCC official said the ministers also discussed the
relations between the chambers of commerce and ministers of
commerce in these countries, economic cooperation between the
GCC states on the one hand and the United States and the
European Union on the other.
</P>
<P>
On the GCC-European cooperation, Al-Hujailan said that the
GCC states should unify custom tariffs and set up a common
market before signing an agreement with the European Union to
establish a free trade zone.
</P>
<P>
The GCC General Secretary pointed out that the GCC-European
balance of trade tilted in favor of the European countries
by 14 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the classification of commodities,
which is blocking the integration of the GCC customs tariffs,
would be finalized at the forthcoming GCC summit due in December
in Abu Dhabi, capital of the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
The GCC, a regional political and economic alliance set up
in 1981, comprises Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia
and the UAE. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
