indispensable. The role should continue regardless of all the
obstacles and the intransigence of Israel's current government,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. attempts to break the Palestinian-Israeli peace
impasse have been hampered by Israel's rejection of a 13 percent
further Israeli redeployment plan.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Mideast Peace Coordinator Dennis Ross kicked off last week
a fresh mission to narrow the gap between both sides. Negotiations
have been deadlocked since March 1997 when Israel began building
settlement in Arab East Jerusalem.


