<HEADLINE> Khamenei Warns against Freedom Abuse by Press </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Iran's supreme leader
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei on Tuesday gave a stern warning to
the press and called on cultural and judicial bodies to deal
with those who are abusing the freedoms.
</P>
<P>
"I keep waiting to see what the responsible bodies will
do" with the group of the press that started targeting the
people's faith, Khamenei said to a group of commanders of
the Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC).
</P>
<P>
The problem arose when a group of people opposed to
Islam, (late supreme leader) Imam (Khomeini) and the system
hid behind another group and started targeting people's faith,
the official news agency IRNA quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
"I see that a group of the press in the country is
gripped with such crisis and they should salvage themselves,"
he warned, "stopping their moves is not anything difficult."
</P>
<P>
It is believed that Khamenei was referring to the
pro-moderate press which are struggling for freedom of
expression in the country, one of the promises of President
Mohammad Khatami during the presidential elections in May last
year.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said that the Ministry of Culture and Islamic
Guidance, judicial and security bodies should identify those who
have targeted the people's faith and have desecrated the
Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
"I am making it clear for the officials that they should
take measures and find out which paper is going beyond the
boundaries of freedom," he said.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei underlined the need to distinguish between proper
exercise of freedoms and conspiracies.
</P>
<P>
"How can one allow those looking towards the west and
specially the U.S., after 20 years of opposition with the
Islamic revolution and the late Imam Khomeini, to raise
questions about the glorious past of the nation?" he
questioned
</P>
<P>
Khamenei also underlined the necessity for preservation of
the system's integrity and respect for the officials and
called for preventing any offenses carried out under the
pretext of defending leadership and religion.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to the recent assault by a group of
hard-liners on two key figures of the Khatami's cabinet,
Minister of Culture and Islamic Guidance Ataollah Mohajerani and
Vice President for Development and Social Affairs Abdollah
Nouri.
</P>
<P>
On September 4, Mohajerani and Nouri were beaten by the
hard-liners in a funeral ceremony for 700 Iranian soldiers
killed in the Iran-Iraq war.
</P>
<P>
"We have rules and regulations and officials and the system
should be respected," the Iranian leader added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
