meetings with Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz and Foreign
Minister Ismail Cem during the visit.
</P>
<P>
Turkish and British defense officials signed an agreement
aimed at strengthening defense industry cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The accord is similar to those Turkey has signed with
other countries in the same sector, Turkish officials said,
declining to give details.
</P>
<P>
Britain currently does not have a significant investment in
Turkey's defense industry apart from a 160 million U.S. dollar
deal on wireless radio production between the Turkish army and
the British company Marconi. 
