<HEADLINE> GCC Ministers Adopt Common Specifications for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Trade ministers of the
Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) adopted here Tuesday plans for
applying common specifications and standards for goods to be
produced and circulated in and among the GCC states.
</P>
<P>
The measures were passed at a meeting of the GCC Board Council
which groups the trade ministers, according to the Kuwait News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Nasser Al-Ajeel, General Director of Kuwait's Public Authority
of Industry, said that the council approved 36 compulsive
standard specifications to be published in the official gazettes
in the GCC countries within six months.
</P>
<P>
The specifications include levels of radiation in food
supplies, milk, chicken, fruits and air conditioners.
</P>
<P>
The council also adopted unified standards for sanitary ware,
pottery, insulation boards, microscopic levels in food and
perfumes.
</P>
<P>
Saudi-proposed conditions for transfer, marketing and storage
of sweet oil were also passed during the council's meeting.
</P>
<P>
The GCC, a regional political and economic alliance
established in 1981, comprises Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar,
Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates. 
</P>
