<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances AIDS and STD Control Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday
approved a 165 million U.S. dollar loan to Brazil to help reduce
the incidence of HIV and STD infection, expand and improve
treatment and care of persons with HIV, AIDS and STDs.
</P>
<P>
The Second AIDS and STD Control Project is planned on the First
AIDS and STD Control Project. Under the first project, the
Brazilian government put in place a prevention program containing
many of the features which have proved to be highly successful in
preventing the spread of HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The new project will broaden prevention activities, maintaining
a focus on high-risk groups. The project will also strengthen
evaluation capacity, work towards the sustainability of the
program, and decentralize some responsibilities for AIDS/STD
prevention to states and municipalities to identify the most
cost-effective intervention.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 300 million
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
