<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays Second Roads Rehabilitation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday
okayed a 85 million U.S. dollar loan to help finance the Second
Roads Rehabilitation Project in Panama.
</P>
<P>
The project will improve road maintenance management,
rehabilitate high-priority, primary, secondary and tertiary roads
as well as reduce traffic congestion in Panama City.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the project will strengthen the capacity of the
Environmental Unit of the Ministry of Public Works for conducting
environmental and social impact assessments and for mitigating the
negative impacts of road development in Panama.
</P>
<P>
The construction and rehabilitation of Panamanian road will
take place throughout the country. In Panama City, commuters will
benefit from road rehabilitation and minor widening, as well as
technical advise to reorganize public transportation to reduce
transport costs and travel time. The rehabilitation of secondary
and tertiary roads will complement poverty alleviation in rural
areas as inhabitants will now have greater access to outside
employment and markets.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 123.8 million
dollars. Apart from the World Bank's loan, the government of
Panama will contribute 38.8 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
