<DOCNO> XIE19980916.0050 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-15 20:31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNRWA Workers Stage One-day Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A majority of the workers at
the United Nations Relief and Works Agency's (UNRWA) branch in
Jordan Tuesday staged a one-day strike to protest low wages
and poor working conditions.
</P>
<P>
The strike was prompted by the cash-strapped agency's recent
decision to raise the salaries of 10 to 15 senior managers in its
five areas of operation by 30 to 40 percent, the official Jordan
Television quoted an anonymous worker at the agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ordinary workers' wages have remained unchanged for some
five years and have been inconsistent with the increase of the
cost of living, he said.
</P>
<P>
"After 10 years of service at the UNRWA, our salaries are
lower than those of government employees. We do not even get the
same benefits of early retirement and compensation for
termination of employment," the semi-official Jordan Times
recently quoted an UNRWA staff representative as saying.
</P>
<P>
The UNRWA's workers have also complained for poor working
conditions and service cutbacks imposed by the agency, according
to the representative.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, UNRWA Commissioner General Peter Hansen has sent
the staff a letter, insisting that the strike would not yield any
results and the workers' salaries were well above those of
the local government employees.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's strike took place after rounds of negotiations between
the workers and the agency's managers.
</P>
<P>
Jordan Television reported Tuesday that similar strikes also
happened in other four areas in the region that the agency
operates.
</P>
<P>
There has been no official figures so far as to how many UNRWA
employees were on strike in Jordan and how many in the whole
region.
</P>
<P>
The UNRWA is currently burdened with a 56 million U.S. dollars
of deficit in its budget of 314 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, the UNRWA has been short of fund as the
traditional contributors began to decrease their donation. The
financial shortage forced the agency to adopt cost-reduction
measures which included suspending recruitment of teachers,
canceling hospitalization programs and reducing international
staff by 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
The UNRWA was established in 1948 to offer educational, health
and other social services to some 3.4 million registered
Palestinian refugees in Jordan, Syria, Lebanon, the West Bank and
Gaza Strip. Jordan alone is home to over 1.2 million
U.N.-registered Palestinian refugees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
