<DOCNO> XIE19980916.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Nepal in Panic Over Adulterated Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Panic is growing in the
Himalayan kingdom of Nepal over adulterated oil in the market as
Dashain, the biggest festival in the country, is just around the
corner.
</P>
<P>
Panic gripped the country about three weeks ago when news broke
out that adulterated mustard oil, which had claimed more than 50
lives and caused over 2,000 cases of dropsy in neighboring India,
was being smuggled into the markets here.
</P>
<P>
Most of the Nepali people, especially those living in urban
areas and the Terai region bordering India, use mustard oil which
is considered cheaper and good for health.
</P>
<P>
Ten out of 278 samples of mustard oil collected from customs
offices in the border area, godowns, oil mills, wholesalers and
retailers had been found adulterated with argemone mexicana, said
Dr. Tika Bahadur Karki, chief of the Central Food Research
Laboratory under the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
And the fatal oil had been detected in a soybean oil sample
taken from Kathmandu and three mustard oil samples from Nepalgunj
in mid-western Nepal, he added.
</P>
<P>
Argemone mexicana, which grows together with mustard in fields,
is a black seed quite similar to mustard seeds in appearance,
press reports here said.
</P>
<P>
Its mixture into the mustard oil can cause symptoms like bouts
of vomiting followed by diarrhea, swelling of the stomach, hands
and legs, cataract in the eyes, urinary disorder, respiratory
complications and even heart attack, Ganga Raj Aryal from the
Department of Health said.
</P>
<P>
The atmosphere of fear and apprehension grew further after 10
members of two families in Jhapa district of eastern Nepal fell
ill after consuming the cooking oil bought in the local market.
</P>
<P>
Experts blamed the infiltration of adulterated oil in the
market on the government's failure to control the sale of
unlabeled food products.
</P>
<P>
Press reports said that the government had issued an order to
label the date of manufacture and expiry, the net weight and batch
number of food products from April 14 this year, but backed down
when the industrialists raised a hue and cry.
</P>
<P>
In the past weeks, the central and local governments in Nepal
have taken strict measures to strengthen checking at border points
to seize smuggled adulterated oil from India, ban import of
cooking oil from India, seal factories producing adulterated oil,
test samples brought from across the country and take actions
against those selling adulterated oil.
</P>
<P>
And a committee has been formed to coordinate efforts of
various ministries toward providing quality cooking oil to the
consumers for the coming festival.
</P>
<P>
The Nepal Vegetable Ghee and Oil Manufacturer Association
announced on Sunday that the adulterated oil would be withdrawn
from the market within three to four days and replaced with oil
certified by the government.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Nepal Food Retailers Association decided not to
sell cooking oil unless it was certified as edible and to have the
wholesalers make the testing of mustard oil public.
</P>
<P>
Most of the consumers in the Kathmandu Valley just have stopped
purchasing the mustard oil. Sales of other kinds of cooking oil
were said to have gone down as well.
</P>
<P>
"I have completely stopped buying any oil from the market after
the incident. I used to buy sunflower oil, but now it is also not
safe because there may be adulteration in it," said Mrs. L.
Sharma, a consumer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
