<HEADLINE> Bumper Rice Harvest for Vietnam Despite Bad Weather </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Despite several natural
disasters, Vietnam's farmers are expecting a 31.3-million-ton
harvest this year, including 28.4 million tons of rice, marking
the fourth straight year of bumper rice crops.
</P>
<P>
According to the General Statistics Department, this year's
rice output is the largest on record, 900,000 tons more than last
year.
</P>
<P>
Despite several months of extended dry spells and extreme heat
waves caused by the El Nino phenomenon along Vietnam's central
coast, farmers in the Mekong delta survived by building field
embankments and coastal dikes to prevent salinization.
</P>
<P>
However, the subsidiary crops' output has dropped slightly
because of the prolonged drought spell to an expected 2.8 million
tons, 200,000 tons fewer than last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
