<HEADLINE> Shanghai Tackles the Year 2000 Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of
Shanghai, China's top industrial center, today set the agenda of
fixing the year 2000 bug, also known as Y2K, in line with the
requirement of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
According to this timetable, Shanghai will have checked and
tested all of its computer systems by the end of this December,
completed fixing work by the end of March next year and checked
and tested all the fixed systems by the end of September 1999.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, a leading city in China in computer application, has
nearly a million computers and a large numbers of embedded chips.
 
</P>
