<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Party Official Reiterates Rural Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Reform in China's rural areas
should be further deepened to help promote national economic
growth, according to Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of the National
People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, the country's
legislative body.
</P>
<P>
Tian, who is also member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), made the call
during an inspection tour of northwest Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region between September 5-15.
</P>
<P>
"We should continue to deepen reforms in the countryside and
guide farmers to readjust their production structure in accordance
with market needs to help increase farmers' incomes and promote
national economic growth," Tian said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the people of all ethnic groups in Xinjiang have
scored considerable achievements on all fronts since the founding
of New China in 1949, especially since the launching of the
national reform and opening-up program 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
"Xinjiang's economic strength has increased and local people's
life has improved significantly," Tian said.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang has great advantages in terms of natural resources and
its development prospects are very bright as long as the people of
various ethnic groups unite as one and work closely round the
center of economic construction, he said.
</P>
<P>
To further develop rural economy, the household responsibility
system should be persevered, Tian noted.
</P>
<P>
He also said the production of grain must never be slackened,
the policy of comprehensive agricultural development must not be
deviated, and the guideline for developing rural and township
enterprises must not be wavered.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture is the foundation of the national economy and only
when the agricultural sector is stable can there by economic and
national stability as well as economic and social advances, Tian
underlined.
</P>
<P>
"In the process to deepen reforms in the rural areas, we must
guide the farmers to be more market-oriented and pursue commodity
production," he said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, efforts must be beefed up to industrialize
the rural economy and seek a combination of trade and the
industrial and agricultural sectors, he added.
</P>
<P>
"To accelerate the industrialization of the agricultural sector
is conducive not only to narrowing the economic disparity between
urban and rural areas but also to accelerating the modernization
process in the rural areas," Tian said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
