<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian government and
parliament have vowed to restore order as soon as possible and
investigate criminal responsibility for the riots which have
wracked the capital over the last few days.
</P>
<P>
At a government meeting on Tuesday, President Fatos Nano
strongly condemned the opposition Democratic Party for allegedly
organizing the armed disturbances on September 13 and 14 in Tirana.
</P>
