September 14 as a "coup" and demanded the Public Order Ministry
bring its organizers and participants to justice.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued on Tuesday night, the parliament accused
Democratic Party chairman Sali Berisha of organizing and
commanding the coup.
</P>
<P>
The parliament also called on the government to take strong
measures to restore safety, peace and normal life in Tirana.
</P>
<P>
Violence erupted in Tirana on September 13 after the murder of
opposition leader Azem Hajdari the previous day and soon
escalated. 
