<HEADLINE> Managers of Moderate Iranian Newspaper Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Some managers of the banned
Iranian moderate evening newspaper Tous were arrested on
Wednesday, Tehran Islamic Revolutionary court announced in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA quoted the statement as saying
that the arrest warrant was issued in light of the activities of
some managers of the newspaper in conflict with the national
security and interests.
</P>
<P>
However, the statement did not give names or number of the
arrested.
</P>
<P>
It said that Tous, which was named after an Iranian ancient
city, was banned from publication as of Wednesday until further
notice.
</P>
<P>
The ban order was announced on Tuesday to Tous' license holder
and editorial director Mohammad Sadeq Javadi Hesar, after Iranian
leader Ayatollah Khamenei on Tuesday called on cultural and
judicial bodies to deal with "the group of the press which are
abusing the freedoms."
</P>
<P>
Tous appeared on newsstands only on July 25 to replace the
banned moderate daily Jameah (Society) and was welcomed by the
public, particularly the Iranian youth for its support for the
policies of President Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
It was banned for the first time on August 1 following strong
protest from the hard-liners and conservatives against its
pro-democracy articles.
</P>
<P>
But the ban was lifted one day after it was announced as
the Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance called on the
conservative judiciary to revoke the ban order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
