<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Irish Prime Minister Visits Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi
met and had a cordial, friendly talk with Irish Prime Minister
Bertie Ahern and his party here this evening.
</P>
<P>
Xu briefed the Irish guests on Shanghai's economic development
in recent years, and expressed the hope that gratifying
achievements will be scored in his city's cooperation with Ireland
in the fields of economy, trade and information technology.
</P>
<P>
Irish Prime Minister Ahern pointed to Shanghai as a thriving
international metropolis whose rapid economic development has left
a deep impression on the world. He also expressed the hope of
establishing a new, long-term cooperative partnership with
Shanghai, especially in such high-tech and information technology
fields as electronics and computer software.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Ahern, who arrived in Shanghai from Beijing this
afternoon, is scheduled to visit the Pudong New Area and the
Shanghai Stock Exchange, and meet with Chinese and foreign
entrepreneurs.  
</P>
