<HEADLINE> Funcinpec Agrees to Attend Cambodian Assembly Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SIEM REAP, Cambodia, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's
deposed First Prime Minister, Prince Norodom Ranariddh, said
Wednesday that his Funcinpec party would participate the first
National Assembly session chaired by King Norodom Sihanouk.
</P>
<P>
After holding talks with Sihanouk on Wednesday in the northern
town of Siem Reap, Prince Ranariddh said, "We discussed the way to
avoid bloodshed and to resolve the current political crisis, but
we did not touch upon the formation of the new government.
</P>
<P>
"Funcinpec party has agreed to participate in the new National
Assembly's first session which is scheduled on September 24 and
will be presided over by the King in Siem Reap."
</P>
<P>
The Prince also hoped to meet Chea Sim, President of the
Cambodian People's Party (CPP), as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia was plunged into a political crisis on July 26 when
the CPP won a majority of parliamentary seats in the general
election, but failed to get the two-thirds majority needed to form
a government alone.
</P>
<P>
The CPP's major rivals, Funcinpec and the Sam Rainsy Party
(SRP) led by former dissident Sam Rainsy, have rejected the result
of the poll which was judged free and fair by international
observers, and accused the CPP of rigging the elections.
</P>
<P>
They also turned down offers of forming a coalition and
threatened not to participate the first session of the new
national assembly.
</P>
<P>
Three weeks of demonstrations in Phnom Penh resulted in violent
clashes involving the police, supporters of Funcinpec, the SRP and
the CPP, which left several dead and injured.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh said that the continuation of the demonstrations
would depend on the outcome of the three-party summit although
Funcinpec had decided to call off the protests in order to pave
the way for the talks expected to take place this weekend.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Sam Rainsy would meet Sihanouk in Siem
Reap on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
