<HEADLINE> Henan's Industrial Sector Rebounds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The industrial sector of
central China's Henan Province rebounded in August, official
statistics indicate.
</P>
<P>
Henan's industrial incremental value totaled 7.27 billion yuan
(876 million U.S. dollars) in August, up 6.9 percent from the same
month of last year. The growth rate is 0.2 percentage points
higher than that for July.
</P>
<P>
Overall, Henan had 57.67 billion yuan in industrial incremental
value in the first eight months of this year, an increase of 5.6
percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Henan's sales totaled 22.24 billion yuan last month,
up 4.5 percent. The monthly industrial production-to-sales ratio
reached 97.11 percent, the highest this year.
</P>
<P>
An official analysis shows that production of 26 of the 50
industrial products, including building materials and chemicals,
increased for the January-August period. Production of crude coal
and oil and some others continued to slide during the period.
</P>
</TEXT>
