<HEADLINE> Chinese Film Festival Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A week-long Chinese Film
Festival opened here Wednesday to mark the 49th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China which falls on October
1.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the inauguration ceremony, Nepali Education Minister
Arjun Narsingh K. C. praised the achievements China has made in
various fields in the past 49 years.
</P>
<P>
He described China as a reliable friend, which has given Nepal
a lot of help in its economic development.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Nepal Zeng Xuyong said that China and
Nepal have conducted fruitful cooperation in political, economic,
commercial, cultural and other fields.
</P>
<P>
