<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Correcting A Few Judicial Workers' Law-Violating Practices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Top Chinese legislator Li
Peng today enumerated a few law-violating activities by judicial
workers in some places and called for prompt actions be taken to
put an end to judicial irregularities.
</P>
<P>
"The violation of regulations in the profession and neglect of
work ethics by some officials in judicial departments are so
serious that it has undermined judicial work and posed a threat to
social stability," warned Li, chairman of the National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, at the fifth meeting of the NPC
interior judicial committee that closed here today.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot afford to waste any time addressing the problem,"
said the chairman.
</P>
<P>
During the past three days, law-makers heard reports by Xiao
Yang, president of the Superem People's Court, and Han Zhubin,
procurator-general of the Superem People's procuratorate, on
rectification work in judicial departments.
</P>
<P>
Judicial corruption, which draws sharp criticism from deputies
at the annual sessions of the National People's Congress over
recent years, has become one of the relevant heated topics by the
general public, said Li.
</P>
<P>
He appreciated the efforts by judicial departments across China
to set standards for the behavior of their staff, and nevertheless
noted that their achievements should not be overestimated.
</P>
<P>
"With the absence of a full-fledged legal framework at work and
the influence of unhealthy practices from inside and outside the
Party, judicial corruption cannot be expected to stamped out at
one stroke or overnight," said Li.
</P>
<P>
Acknowledging that fighting against judicial corruption is a
long-term task, he said that courts and procurator's offices at
all levels should, in line with specific local conditions,
conscientiously sum up experiences and come to recognize the
importance and protractedness of the work, so that they will pool
efforts to do a good job in education and rectification.
</P>
<P>
While going in for education and straightening things out, the
judicial departments should do their work well, and improve it in
the course of conducting reforms, and build up and strengthen
their ranks and further improve their work system, he said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from system building and ideological education, he noted,
the question of prime importance is to safeguard judicial fairness
and to guarantee that preliminary trials be open to the public and
the people's jury system be instituted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, special efforts should be enhanced to stop the
practice of prolonged detention and stalling handling of cases, Li
said. He also urged the people's congresses at all levels to
increase their supervision over judicial work as a means to
further promote judicial fairness.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
