<HEADLINE> Germany Leads Mine-Clearing Operation off Baltic Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Naval units from Germany and ten
other European countries have launched an operation off the Baltic
coast of Estonia to clear mines deployed since World War II, the
German Defense Ministry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 11-nation operation, involving 800 seamen from Estonia,
Lithuania, Latvia, Belgium, Denmark, Germany, Finland, the
Netherlands, Norway and Poland, was launched in the spirit of
NATO's Partnership for Peace program and is the fourth such
operation since 1996.
</P>
<P>
Three previous operations in the region removed and destroyed
61 explosive objects, including torpedoes, bombs, and floating
mines, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
This year's mine-clearing operation started on Tuesday and is
due to end on September 21. 
</P>
