<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Finnish Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao, during a meeting with visiting Finnish Foreign Minister
Tarja Halonen here today, said that the Chinese government values
its ties with Finland and appreciates the efforts made by the
Finnish government to advance Finnish-Chinese relations.
</P>
<P>
China is ready to make concerted effort with Finland to promote
Sino-Finnish friendly cooperative relations, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
The recent years have witnessed the friendly cooperation in all
areas between China and Finland, with exchange of high-level
visits increasing which has enhanced mutual understanding and
promoted bilateral relations, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the world is moving towards multi-polarization
along with the globalization of economy, adding that the
strengthening of Sino-Finnish cooperation in international affairs
would not only serve the interests of the two peoples, but also
benefit the Asia-Europe and Sino-European collaboration.
</P>
<P>
Halonen said that Finland is concerned with the development of
China, which plays an important role in Asia and the world as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of Finland and China have had frequent exchange of
visits and exchanged views in recent years, with bilateral
economic and trade cooperation going smoothly, Halonen said.
</P>
<P>
Finland is pleased with the establishment of the good
relationship with such an important country as China, Halonen told
Hu, adding that the Finnish side hopes to further promote
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Hu also briefed the Finnish visitors on the current political
and economic situation in China.  
</P>
