<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Cardboard Producer Being Built in Ningbo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, September 16 (Xinhua) -- China will soon start
third-phase construction of a cardboard production base which will
be the largest of its kind in Asia upon completion.
</P>
<P>
This facility, underway in Ningbo in east China's Zhejiang
Province, is a joint venture of the China Paper Industry Group,
the Ningbo Light Industry Group and a Singapore paper company.
</P>
<P>
The first two construction phases have cost 4 billion yuan and
have a combined annual production capacity of 500,000 tons of
cardboard. The third phase will cost another 12 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The plant will have a production capacity of 260,000 tons of
food packaging board, 300,000 tons of fancy paperboard, and
440,000 tons of corrugated board when completed in 2001. By then,
the production base will turn out 1.5 million tons of cardboard a
year.
</P>
<P>
The city is offering 26 auxiliary projects for cooperation
with overseas investors. These projects involve a total investment
of 660 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
