<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nine People Imprisoned for Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Defendants in a fraud case
involving casings for pork livers and sheep entrails were recently
sentenced to imprisonment in central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Yueyang City Intermediate People's Court in Hunan sentenced
Zhou Zhenglong to life imprisonment and the deprivation of
political rights for life. The court also confiscated his personal
property valued at 60,000 yuan (about 7,500 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Eight other defendants received prison sentences ranging from
8-15 years, with periods for deprivation of political rights
ranging from 1-5 years. The court also confiscated their their
personal properties in amounts ranging from 20,000-50,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The defendants from the cities of Xiangyin and Xiangtan in
Hunan Province and unscrupulous business people from Hong Kong,
Macao, Taiwan regions and Malaysia conspired to defraud tens of
millions of yuan from Chinese export enterprises under the pretext
of exporting casings for pork livers and sheep entrails.
</P>
<P>
The group defrauded 38 Chinese enterprises in 16 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions between 1992 and 1966.
</P>
<P>
The 34 separate instances of fraud involved 48.77 million yuan
(5.86 million U.S. dollars), and burdened both the state and
victimized enterprises with financial losses totalling 40.71
million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
