<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Zone Witnesses Flourishing Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The development of new and
high technology has enabled the state-level Fuzhou Development
Zone (FDZ), located in the capital of southeast China's Fujian
Province, to maintain a high growth rate for three consecutive
years.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics indicate that the zone's industrial output
has grown by 33.6 percent annually since 1995, with 1997 output
topping 10 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The zone, established in 1992, consists of a bonded district, a
Taiwan region investment zone, a hi-tech park and an agricultural
experimental zone which is jointly managed by agronomists from
inland areas and Taiwan region.
</P>
<P>
The zone's management committee has increased investments in
hi-tech development annually over the past three years, with the
1997 figure hitting 3.23 million yuan. The committee has also
established a special fund to finance hi-tech projects.
</P>
<P>
The 23,000 professionals working in the FDZ account for
approximately 15 percent of the zone's total employees.
</P>
<P>
The zone's 78 enterprises engaged in hi-tech production have
developed 373 hi-tech products, including 32 items which have
reached advanced international levels.
</P>
<P>
The flourishing hi-tech industry has attracted a constantly
increasing number of investors from abroad. Fifty-three joint
ventures established in the zone in the first six months of the
year involved total contracted overseas investments of 230 million
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
