<HEADLINE> Nigeria Calls for Improved Relations With World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Head of State,
General Abdulsalami Abubakar has appealed to the World Bank to
normalize relations with his country without further delay.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar made the call Tuesday in Nigerian capital Abuja while
receiving the bank's Vice-President for Africa, Jean-Louis
Sorbib.
</P>
<P>
He said it was imperative for Nigeria to work together with
the World Bank for the mutual advantage of both parties.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar stressed the need for donor countries to reconsider
the problem of debt burden of Nigeria, adding that there was a
real need to return to the Paris Club for a meaning discussion of
the issue of debt relief.
</P>
<P>
Noting that political stability is a necessary pre-requisite
for foreign participation in any national economy, he said the
window of investment opportunities would remain opened for the
mutual benefits of prospective investors in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar stressed that progress being made in the political
front must be accompanied by corresponding progress in the
economic realm.
</P>
<P>
He, therefore, called on the international community to avail
themselves of the new investment opportunities in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
In his response, Sarbib said it is important for the World
Bank to work in partnership with Nigeria for accelerated economic
development in the country, which he described as "the beacon of
hope for African Renaissance and new hope as the greatest
ingredient of investment."
</P>
<P>
Sarbib said the international business community is happy
under General Abubakar as the country is on the path of political
stability and economic growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
