<HEADLINE> Flood-Ravaged Province Vows to Attain Economic Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang Province, an area
which suffered from some of the most severe devastation during the
summer flooding, has pledged to work diligently over remaining four
months of the year to achieve the annual economic growth target of
an 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that over 2,000 industrial firms
sustained flood damage totalling three billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The August industrial output value for Heilongjiang, a leading
heavy industrial center in northeast China, fell by 1.5 billion
yuan, with an accompanying 520 million yuan drop in industrial
value-added.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government plans to increase the production of
building materials, textiles, pharmaceuticals and foodstuffs in
order to increase the industrial output value by 2.7 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang also plans to carry out agricultural and water
control projects at cost a 14.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province will close a number of firms with ineffective
management and merge various other ventures in order to optimize
the industrial structure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
