<HEADLINE> Share Prices Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices shot up with
active buying on the Singapore Stock Market Wednesday as the
benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) climbed by 44.47 points to
close at 946.75.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed the surge to rising hopes of international
action to lower interest rates and spur global growth.
</P>
<P>
They said the rise was sparked by a falling interest rates
environment and mounting speculation that Singapore's weight in
the Morgan Stanley Capital International Indexes will be
increased.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 302.73 million units worth 351.8 million
Singapore dollars (about 203.94 million U.S. dollars). Advances
outnumbered declines by 210 to 55 with 322 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
KepLand was the most active stock of the day as it had 20.42
million stocks traded. It was followed by Wing T that had 17.8
million units done. SingTel was next with 11.92 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS F was the top gainer of the day as it climbed 70 cents to
close at 6.05 Singapore dollars. SIA F moved up 70 cents as well
and finished at 8.8 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem was up 50 cents
to end at 6.6 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day
as it lost 30 cents to close at 17.7 Singapore dollars. Jurship
slid 20 cents to finish at 6.2 Singapore dollars and TLB Land shed
17 cents to end at 0.65 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
