<HEADLINE> Beijing-Taiwan Trade Fair Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A trade fair on the
commercialization of scientific research results in both Taiwan
and Beijing opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Shun Fuling, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), and
Chen Yunling, director of the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State
Council, attended the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Mayor Jia Qingling delivered an opening address
extending a welcome to some 300 Taiwan scholars and guests from
the island province's industrial and commercial sectors.
</P>
<P>
Beijing and Taiwan have respective advantages in the high-tech
field, and this lays a solid foundation for further cooperation
between the two sides, he said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of July, Beijing had approved 1,572 Taiwanese-funded
projects, with a contractual investment of 1.91 billion
U.S. dollars. Among these are more than 400 hi-tech projects, with
a contractual investment of 200 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The three-day trade fair will include reporting sessions,
research-results trade, academic discussions and observation
tours. Four hundred twenty-nine projects will be discussed during
the fair covering the fields of electronic information, modern
agriculture, food, textiles, building materials, and environmental
protection.  
</P>
