<DOCNO> XIE19980916.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 400 Houses Destroyed in Riot in Riau, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- At least 400 shops, houses
and hotels were destroyed by fire in a riot in Bagansiapi-Api town
in Bengkalis district, Riau province in Indonesia's northern
Sumatra island Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The riot broke out at about 8 p.m. on Tuesday night when
hundreds of people from all directions suddenly organized
themselves into a mob and went to the town, damaging shops and
setting them on fire, according to Antara News Agency reports.
</P>
<P>
The fire had not been put out until Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
"We, the community members, and the security apparatus tried
our best to drive them away but to no avail because we were
outnumbered by the mob pouring forth from everywhere", Antara
quoted a resident as saying.
</P>
<P>
No report on casualties and losses from the riot and looting
has been made available.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a strike staged by drivers of public vehicles has
paralyzed Samarinda, capital of East Kalimantan province,
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to Antara News Agency, the drivers were demanding
lower prices of spare parts and a review of overlapping routes.
</P>
<P>
The strike started at 10:30 a.m., causing hundreds of commuters
to be stranded in the city, the reports added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
