<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus hit by Slight Tremors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Two slight earth tremors
hit Cyprus during the past 24 hours and no injuries or damage were
reported so far.
</P>
<P>
According to the Geological Survey Department Wednesday, the
first quake measuring 4.4 on the Richter scale occurred at 2150
local time (1850 GMT) Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The second was recorded at 0113 Wednesday (2213 GMT Tuesday)
and measured 4.3 on the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
Both quakes were felt in the southern town of Limassol and the
western town of Paphos. The epicenter was in the sea, some 20
kilometers south of Paphos.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, an earthquake measuring 6.1 on the Richter scale hit
the island, injuring more than 50 people, damaging many houses in
Limassol and Paphos.
</P>
<P>
A total of 67 people were killed in earthquakes in the past 100
years in Cyprus, which is situated in the second major seismic
zone in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980916.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manufacturers Urged to Support Family Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The State Family Planning
Committee (SFPC) today called on manufacturers and wholesalers of
reproductive healthcare products to support family planning effort
in flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Family planning organizations in Jiangxi, Hunan, Hubei,
Heilongjiang, Jilin provinces and the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region have sustained heavy losses as a result of summer flooding,
according to SFPC Director Zhang Weiqing.
</P>
<P>
Medicines and basic reproductive health care products are badly
needed in flood-stricken areas, especially poverty-stricken areas,
to guarantee the fulfillment of this year's family planning
program, said Zhang.
</P>
<P>
Ten enterprises, including the Zhuhai Well Medical Instruments
Corp. and the Kimberly-Clark (China) Holding Co., have donate
related products valued at 5.3 million yuan (638,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Family planning departments at all levels will distribute
donated products to affected areas at the earliest possible date,
according to Zhang.
</P>
<P>
Heavy flooding since early summer have caused devastation in
six provinces and autonomous regions along the Yangtze,
Songhuajiang and Nenjiang rivers. Devastating floods have killed
over 3,000 people, adversely affected the lives of 200 million
Chinese citizens and led to economic losses of well over 160
billion yuan (18 billion US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980916.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Celebrates International Ozone Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- China, one of the largest
producers and consumers of ozone-depleting substances (ODS) in the
world, held activities today to mark the fourth International
Ozone Day and advance the cause of ozone-layer protection.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 delegates from organizations including the Executive
Committee of the Multilateral Fund under the Montreal Protocol,
the United Nations Development Program, the United Nations
Environment Program, the State Environmental Protection
Administration, the State Development Planning Commission, and the
Ministry of Science and Technology attended today's ceremony.
</P>
<P>
According to the Montreal Protocol on Substances which deplete
the ozone layer, China will stop the production and consumption of
ODS by July 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
With only nine months remaining to reach this goal, China is
facing more pressing issues at present, Wang Jirong, deputy
director of the State Environmental Protection Administration,
told today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Many medium-sized and small enterprises have become the main
obstacles in the process of phasing out ODS in China, since they
lack financial support and managerial expertise, according to Wang.
</P>
<P>
She said China plans to revise its regulations and work out new
policies to tackle the problems.
</P>
<P>
Since the United Nations declared September 16 as International
Ozone Day in 1995, China has held activities to mark it every year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 100 children were given awards today for their
paintings on the theme of ozone-layer protection, and two of the
children will take part in a contest held by the United Nations
Environment Program on the same subject.
</P>
<P>
An ozone-monotoring balloon lifted off here today to obtain
data on the ozone content in the atmosphere 20 to 30 kilometers
above the earth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
