<DOCNO> XIE19980916.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Maintains Steady Economic Growth Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province maintained stable economic growth during the first eight
month's of this year in spite of declining exports resulting from
the impact of the ongoing financial crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, one of the nation's major contributors to foreign
trade, accounted for close to 40 percent of total exports. The
adverse influences of the international environment limited the
province's export growth to only 8.1 percent for the first eight
months, down dramatically by 25.6 percent growth for 1997. The
growth figure reached 1.5 percent in August.
</P>
<P>
However, the negative impact of sluggish exports was offset by
a relatively impressive 19.2 percent rise in investments in
infrastructure and technological renovations, with total
investments for the period surpassing 62.32 billion yuan (7.5
billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector provided additional encouragement, with
the sector's value-added growing by 9.9 percent to 155.9 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales for consumer products grew by 12.7 percent in real
terms.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's gross domestic product (GDP) for the period grew by
9.7 percent, some seven percent higher than the national average,
with 10 percent growth for industrial value-added surpassing the
national figure by 7.9 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
