<HEADLINE> AL to Present New Initiative on Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) will
present a new initiative on Somalia at the 110th session of the AL
Foreign Ministerial Council conference, which is to be held in
Cairo Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
AL Assistant Secretary General Ahmed bin Hilli said that the
impetus for the new initiative was based on an agreement signed
last month by rival factions of the Somali National Alliance and the
26-faction National Salvation Council.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for the establishment of a federal
government and the reopening of Somalia's airports and seaports.
</P>
<P>
Since the ouster of the late dictator Mohamed Siad Barre in
1991, Somalia has been fragmented into fiefdoms protected by
faction leaders, who fought to expand their turfs despite a number
of peace agreements.
</P>
<P>
The AL had lobbied its 22 members to fund a peace conference in
Somali capital Mogadishu and hlep reconstruct the country's
airports and seaports damaged during the six-year-old conflicts.
</P>
<P>
But only 400,000 U.S. dollars of 6 million needed have been
raised so far due to "a lack of confidence" among the AL members
in the sincerity of Somali warring parties in making peace.



16/09/98 8:39 GMT

NNNN
16:36 16:36 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
