<HEADLINE> Foreign Investors Favor Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Businesses from Europe and
the United States have reinforced their investments in Tianjin,
the largest port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
A municipal government official said that during the
January-August period, United States enterprises increased
investments by 25 percent over the same period last year, and
European Union member countries invested 180 million U.S. dollars
in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The official also noted that up to now Tianjin has approved
over 12,000 foreign-funded enterprises, with total investments of
21.9 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, foreign interests put 3.5 billion
U.S. dollars into Tianjin annually.
</P>
<P>
By August, Tianjin had nearly 1,900 U.S.- funded enterprises
with investments totalling three billion U.S. dollars, accounting
for 15 percent of the city's total. The United States is second
only to Hong Kong in Tianjin investment.
</P>
<P>
Six of the top ten enterprises in the United States have
invested in Tianjin, and most have realized satisfactory profits.
Motorola for example, garnered over 160 million U.S. dollars in
profits from Tianjin in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the favorable investment environment and preferential
policies provided by the Tianjin municipal government, most
foreign enterprises have confidence in their investments in the
city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
