<HEADLINE> Dehui Establishes Organic Food Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The city of Dehui in
northeast China's Jilin Province has emerged as one of China's
major production centers for organic food.
</P>
<P>
The Dexin Company, the city's leading organic food producer
which entered operations early this year, has been unable to fully
satisfy increasing demand. Nonetheless, the company has succeeded
in exporting products to Saudi Arabia, Iran and Russia.
</P>
<P>
The company marketed 3,600 tons of beef during the first half
of the year. The ready market provided a 300 US dollar per ton
price for beef over the past three months.
</P>
<P>
The city's Organic Food Festival offered eight varieties of
pollution-free food products, including chicken, beef, edible oil,
rice, vegetables, maize and beans.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the city's organic food producers received orders
valued at 750 million yuan and signed contracts worth over 30
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Constantly improving living standards in China over the past
few years have expanded the market for organic food products.
</P>
<P>
China has 600 registered organic food companies which market
1,200 varieties of organic food products. China's annual export
volume for organic products stands at 20 billion US dollars,
according to Liu Lianfu, director of the China Green Food Center.
</P>
</TEXT>
