<HEADLINE> Tang Jiaxuan Holds Talks with Finnish Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan held talks here today with his Finnish counterpart, Tarja
Halonen.
</P>
<P>
The two engaged in an in-depth exchange of views on bilateral
ties and international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Tang noted the excellent development in Sino-Finnish relations
and frequent reciprocal visits by high-ranking leaders from the
two nations. "The visits have played an important role in
strengthening understanding and promoting cooperation," said Tang.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries have developed sound economic and
trade ties, and have engaged in active cultural, scientific and
technological exchanges.
</P>
<P>
"The two nations are free of fundamental conflicts," said Tang,
adding that China and Finland share either similar or identical
views on major international issues.
</P>
<P>
He expressed China's appreciation of the Finnish government's
stance on the "One China policy," and voiced hope for expanded
friendly and cooperative relations in wide-ranging areas.
</P>
<P>
Halonen said Finland is pleased with the development of
bilateral relations and fully anticipates the further development
of comprehensive ties. She said Finland treasures bilateral ties
and will continue to adhere to "One China policy."  
