<HEADLINE> Reemployment Centers Serve Laid-off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 6,200
reemployment service centers in central China's Henan Province
have provided services for over 610,000 laid-off workers, or 61
percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The province has raised 67 million yuan (8.3 million US
dollars) to help maintain basic living standards for laid-off
workers. Some 120,000 laid-off workers have received basic living
subsidies and some 20,000 workers received monthly subsidies of 300
yuan during August.
</P>
<P>
The provincial labor department has made arrangements to
guarantee the basic living requirements of laid-off workers and
has attempted to establish reemployment service centers in all
state-owned enterprises. Some 150,000 laid-off workers found new
jobs during the first half of this year. 
</P>
