<HEADLINE> Egypt's Hackers Steal Porn Films on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 16 (Xinhua) --- In a first case of
Internet-related crime in Egypt, two computer hackers used a
stolen credit number to download pornographic pictures and films
worth 147,000 dollars, an Egyptian newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette quoted security sources as saying Tuesday
that the two suspects, both college students in the Mediterranean
city of Port Said, have been arrested by police.
</P>
<P>
They were charged with theft after the credit card's holder
complained about the bill.
</P>
<P>
Authorities contacted the cabinet's Internet department, which
is in charge of all Internet service providers, and traced the two
students who had been using the card for seven months.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the incident was the first case of
Internet-related crime in the country, where more and more young
people are getting addicted to surfing on the Internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
