<HEADLINE> Listed Companies in Guangdong Witness Technical Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The listed companies of
Guangdong Province in south China have consistently reported
technical progress in
their efforts to become more efficient.
</P>
<P>
Just recently the Yue Meidi company, an electronics producer,
invested 16 million U.S. dollars to import an advanced production
line for manufacturing washing machines, an innovation expected to
add 150 million yuan (18.07 million U.S. dollars) to the company's
annual output.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Gree Electrics, a major air conditioner
producer, also made a huge outlay to import advanced technology
and equipment from abroad. In the first half of this year, Gree's
sales rose by 30 percent to rank it first in China.
</P>
<P>
Zhongxing Telecommunications in Shenzhen spends about
10 percent of its sales income on scientific research and
development. Last year, they spent 130 million yuan and
this year they expect this figure to reach 300 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Another electronics producer, Kelong, which is listed on the
Hong Kong exchange, set up a research institute in Japan and
employs development experts from Japan, Europe and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Some listed companies in Guangdong have endowed scholarships at major
universities to specially train personnel who will eventually work
for them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
