<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits 63rd Home Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Mark McGwire hit his
record 63rd home run, breaking a tie with Sammy Sosa when he
connected as a pinch-hitter in the first game of a doubleheader
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
McGwire's home run ay broke 62nd home run off Chicago's Steve
Trachsel on September 8. Sosa homered twice Sunday to tie McGwire
at 62.
</P>
<P>
McGwire didn't start the first game of the match against
Pittsburgh, but batted in the ninth and got his sixth career
pinch homer, a 385-foot drive to left-center. 
</P>
