<HEADLINE> China Stopped from Title Clean-Sweep </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Turkey stopped China from a
clean-sweep of six titles by stealing the men's obstacles relay
race, the last event of the 46th Military Pentathlon World
Championships here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
But the Chinese managed to claim other five trophies after
their women's team beat Denmark in the final of the women's
obastacles relay to take the title with a time of one minute
58.53 seconds.
</P>
<P>
China's men's quartet also lost to Ecuador in the semi-final
when the last pentathlete Qin Hongtao made a mistake at his first
obstacle.
</P>
<P>
Turkey, who knocked out Portugal in the other semi-final,
defeated Ecuador in the final to win the relay at 1:49.31.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador finished second by 05.35 behind the winners, a time
that was also slower than third placer China, who ran 1:52.58 in
the 3-4 playoff.
</P>
<P>
"We expected to take all the six gold medals," China's team
leader Jiao Liming said. "I believe we could win the men's race
if we had made into the final." 
</P>
