<HEADLINE> Dike, Ring-road Are to Be Built Around Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government
plans to construct a 50-kilometer-long embankment, a ring-road and
a waterway encircling Dhaka to protect the capital city from
flooding as well as to develop the traffic and transport system of
the ever-expanding metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The plan was announced by Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina while
addressing a gathering of marooned people from a speed boat
Tuesday, The New Nation daily reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The embankment, which can be turned later into a ring- road
having connections with Mirpur embankment (in the northwest part
of the city), will stretch from Tongi (18 kilometers north of
Dhaka) to the northeastern city of Demra, Hasina said.
</P>
<P>
The government also plans to set up a circular railway on the
ring-road to ease the traffic congestion in the city, she said,
adding that a circular waterway will also be developed along the
ring-road in the future.
</P>
<P>
Dhaka has been severely affected in the over two-month-long
floods with more than two-thirds of the city's area inundated and
the traffic system almost totally paralyzed.
</P>
</TEXT>
