<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE -- The Czech economy is declining this year and the
overall situation continues to deteriorate, the State Statistical
Bureau said Monday.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time in five years the Czech economy has
experienced a downturn.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Bureau show the gross domestic
product (GDP) in the first half of 1998 was 592.8 billion Czech
Korun (19.1 billion U.S. dollars), 1.7 percent less than the same
period last year. (Czech-Economy)
</P>
