<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Russia Clarify Borders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine and Russia have already
settled some of their differences over the location of their land
borders since the two neighbors started negotiations on April 1, a
Ukraine official said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Ukrainian Ambassador Yury
Kostenko said the two countries have clarified 750 kilometers of
land borders that stretch eastward from Chernigov to Belgorod.
</P>
<P>
As Ukraine's chief negotiator, Kostenko said the two countries
have finished three rounds of talks on the location of
borders. Ukraine and Russia share a land border of about 2,300
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
However, Kostenko voiced disappointment that Russia refuses to
clearly demarcate marine borders on the Azov Sea.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine insists that all borders, including marine borders,
should be clearly marked on maps, he reiterated, adding that the
borders between Ukraine and Russia are still friendly.
</P>
<P>
The two former Soviet republics will begin their fourth round
of talks on September 23. 
</P>
