<HEADLINE> 3,000 AIDS Cases Registered in Sao Paulo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The first eight months
of the year saw 3,000 new cases of acquired immune deficiency
syndrome (AIDS) in the Brasilian state of Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
The newly registered cases, said the state Health Ministry on
Tuesday, brought the number of people with the deadly disease
there from 65,300 in last January to 68,300 in last August.
</P>
<P>
Out of the accumulative total, 53,500 are men.
</P>
<P>
However, the ministry said the number of new cases in the state
has started to go down since 1995, thanks to preventive and
educational measures taken by authorities.
</P>
<P>
An annual increase of over 8,900 new AIDS cases in the state of
Sao Paulo was projected in 1995, but 6,180 new cases were actually
registered in 1997. 
</P>
