<HEADLINE> European Organizations: Stop Violence in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Major European organizations
have made an appeal to all sides in Albania to stop use of force,
according to a press release distributed by the Austrian Foreign
Ministry Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The European Union, the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) and the Western European Union (WEU)
strongly condemned the violence in Albania, which was touched off
by the slaying of a leading opposition deputy in parliament Azem
Hajdari last weekend.
</P>
<P>
Representing the EU, the OSCE and the WEU, Austrian Foreign
Minister Wolfgang Schuessel, Polish Foreign Minister Bronislav
Geremek and Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini stressed in a
statement that political goals could not be realized by stirring
up riots and instability.
</P>
<P>
They urged Albania's political forces to support President
Rexhep Mejdani's efforts to resolve the crisis and asked the
Albanian government to protect civilians and restore social peace
and order.
</P>
<P>
The chiefs of the three European organizations stressed the
only way out of the current crisis was for the Albanian forces to
work together.
</P>
<P>
Otherwise, they warned, the crisis would deteriorate, the
nation slip once again to the brink of a civil war and the
national economy suffer serious damages. 
</P>
