<HEADLINE> Recyclable Food Boxes Developed in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Derong Paper
Products Co. Ltd., has developed environmentally-sound recyclable
fast-food containers which can decompose in 90 days under natural
conditions.
</P>
<P>
The containers, which are produced with a combination of straw,
reeds and sugarcane pulp, are corrosion-free, oil resistant and
nontoxic. The containers also feature good heat retention
qualities.
</P>
