<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Set up New Industrial Development Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia plans to transform
five islands located off Aceh province near Malaysia into a new
industrial development region, the Indonesian Observer reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian President B.J. Habibie will inaugurate Sabang and
four other islands as an Integrated Economic Development Zone on
September 26, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Agency for the Assessment and Application of Technology
(BPPT) has been aware of the economic potential of Sabang, Weh,
Breueh, Nasi and Teunom since January 1996, and has been
developing infrastructure on these islands since then, said Herman
Ediyanto, chairman of the BPPT technical team overseeing the
development plan.
</P>
<P>
He said the region will concentrate on three main industries:
manufacturing, tourism and fisheries.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Iskandar, an official of the Aceh
administration, as saying that 47 memorandums of understanding had
been signed by the Sabang Development Authority and investors who
will become involved in the new industrial region.
</P>
<P>
Iskandar said supporting facilities are now ready for use,
including roads, ports, an airport, a telecommunications network
and electricity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
