<HEADLINE> Brazil's Auto Exports Down 15.86 Percent in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's auto exports
in August were down 15.86 percent from the same period of last
year, said the Brazilian Vehicle Builders Association.
</P>
<P>
The country's overseas auto sales amounted to 31,047 units in
August, off 5,853 units from a year ago, the association, known as
ANFAVEA, was quoted as saying by the local press on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Compared to the previous month, the August figure represented a
fall of 9.14 percent. In July, auto exports reached 34,169 units.
</P>
<P>
Capable of turning out 2.07 million units a year, Brazil is a
major car producer in Latin America, and its auto exports earned
the country an equivalent of 4.8 billion U.S. dollars in 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
