<HEADLINE> Brazil Increases Steel Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Brazil, the seventh
largest steel producer in the world, increases its steel imports
annually, the Brazilian Institute of Steel said.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted the institute as saying Tuesday that
steel imports are expected to rise from 377,000 tons in 1997 to
790,000 this year.
</P>
<P>
The institute reported that during the period of January to the
present, the national imports of steel products were up 46
percent from the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Steel imports are equal to 5.2 percent of the country's total
steel production, but two years ago it was only 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Brazil produces 25 million tons of steel every year, the
biggest one in Latin America and the seventh in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
