<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Condemns Murdering of Iranian Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Romania condemns the
murdering of Iranian diplomats in Afghanistan by Taliban militia,
said the Foreign Ministry in a release Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The killing of Iranian diplomats is in flagrant violation of
the international rights and basis humanitarian principles, the
release said, stressing that Romania, alongside the international
community, is for the initiation without delay of investigations
for tracing the perpetrators and bringing them before court.
</P>
<P>
Iran had reported 10 diplomats and one official reporter
missing after the Taliban raided, on August 8, the Iranian
consulate in Mazar-e-Sharif, Afghanistan. Lately, Iran stated that
the Taliban militia is responsible for the killing of Iranian
diplomats, after a Taliban spokesman announced that the group has
found nine bodies of the missing Iranian diplomats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
