<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Postpones Referee Training Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The latest casualties of
the NBA lockout are the referee training camp and rookis
transition program, which were both postponed indefinitely on
Tuesday by the league.
</P>
<P>
A lack of progress between the NBA and the Player Association
in reaching a new collective bargaining agreement has resulted in
the postponements. The referee training camp was scheduled to
begin on September 25, while the rookie transition program was
set for September 20 to 23.
</P>
<P>
"Until we have a better idea of when the season start, there
is no point in conducting training camp for the referees or
holding a transition program for rookies, " said NBA deputy
commissioner Russ Granik.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's announcement comes five days after a preseason game
calling off between the Miami Heat and Israeli champion Maccabi
Elite TelAviv scheduled for October 12, marking the first
cancellation in league history.
</P>
<P>
The sides currently are awaiting a grievance ruling from
arbitrator John Feerick. The NBA Players Association filed a
salary grievance hours before the owners imposed a lockout on
July 1.
</P>
<P>
The final briefs for the grievance hearing are due Friday and
Feerick has 30 days after that to render a decision. Although he
is expected to rule before that, the start of the 1998-99 season
is in serious jeopardy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
