<HEADLINE> Romania's 1st Private Investment Abroad Financed by Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Bank for
Development approved a loan of 6.23 million U.S. dollars to
dye-maker Policolor Corporation for the purchase of the majority
share package of a company in Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
The national Rompres news agency reported the event Tuesday by
quoting a release of the bank.
</P>
<P>
It is the first project financed by a Romanian bank allowing a
Romanian private company to purchase the majority share package in
a foreign company. The credit covers 70 percent of the value of
the 51 percent controlling stake held by Orgachim-Ruse, the most
important dye-maker in Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
As a result of this purchase, Policolor acquires new business
markets in Bulgaria, besides those in Russia, Ukraine, the
Republic of Moldova and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The Policolor shares are transacted on Category I of the
Bucharest Stock Exchange and are some of the most important on the
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
