<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Ukraine's Enterprise, Financial Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday
approved two loans totaling 600 million U.S. dollars for a second
enterprise development adjustment project and a financial sector
adjustment project for Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The second enterprise development adjustment project will
support the government's privatization, capital markets
development, accounting reform, bankruptcy reform and deregulation
programs.
</P>
<P>
The financial sector adjustment project will underpin Ukraine's
macroeconomic reform program with a comprehensive set of policy
measures designed to enhance the financial sector, with a special
emphasis on the banking system. This loan will be disbursed in
three tranches: the first disbursement will occur following loan
effectiveness, and the second and third will take place when the
specified policy actions are implemented in December 1998 and June
1999 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Since Ukraine joined the World Bank in 1992, commitments total
over 2.6 billion dollars for 15 projects, including two
guarantees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
