<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Okays Third Annual ESAF Loan for Burkina Faso </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) Tuesday announced the approval of the third annual
arrangement for Burkina Faso under the Enhanced Structural
Adjustment Facility (ESAF) in an amount of 18 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The concessional loan is provided to support the government's
economic program covering July 1998-June 1999. The loan is made
available in two equal semiannual installments, the first of which
can be drawn on September 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
The main macroeconomic objectives of the program for 1998-99
include achievement of real GDP growth of about 6 percent in 1998
and 1999, an average annual inflation rate of 2.5 percent over the
two years, and a narrowing of the external current account deficit
to 10.2 percent of GDP in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Burkina Faso joined the IMF in May 1963. Its quota is about 60
million dollars and its outstanding use of IMF financing currently
totals about 102 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
